'''José Pedro Balmaceda Pascal''' ({{IPA-es|xoˈse ˈpeðɾo βalmaˈseða pasˈkal}}; born April 2, 1975) is a <!--Do not add any links, please see WP:OVERLINK.-->Chilean-born American<!--No hyphen, as that may imply his ethnicity. This is about his nationalities.--> actor. After nearly two decades of taking small roles in film and television, Pascal rose to prominence for portraying [[Oberyn Martell]] during the [[Game of Thrones (season 4)|fourth season]] of the [[HBO]] fantasy series ''[[Game of Thrones]]'' (2014) and [[Javier Peña]] in the [[Netflix]] crime series ''[[Narcos]]'' (2015–2017). Since 2019, he has starred as [[The Mandalorian (character)|the title character]] in the [[Disney+]] ''[[Star Wars]]'' series ''[[The Mandalorian]]'' and again in ''[[The Book of Boba Fett]]'' (2022). Since 2023, he has played [[Joel (The Last of Us)|Joel Miller]] in the HBO drama series ''[[The Last of Us (TV series)|The Last of Us]]''. ''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]'' magazine named him one of the [[Time 100|100 most influential people in the world]] in 2023.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://time.com/collection/100-most-influential-people-2023/ |title=Time 100 |magazine=[[Time (magazine)|Time]] |date=April 13, 2023 |access-date=April 13, 2023 |archive-date=April 13, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230413151502/https://time.com/collection/100-most-influential-people-2023/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

Outside of television, Pascal has appeared in the films ''[[The Adjustment Bureau]]'' (2011), ''[[The Great Wall (film)|The Great Wall]]'' (2016), ''[[Kingsman: The Golden Circle]]'' (2017), ''[[The Equalizer 2]]'' (2018), ''[[Triple Frontier (film)|Triple Frontier]]'' (2019), ''[[Wonder Woman 1984]]'' (2020), and ''[[The Unbearable Weight of Massive Talent]]'' (2022).

==Early life==
{{see also|Allende family|Balmaceda family}}

José Pedro Balmaceda Pascal was born on April 2, 1975, in [[Santiago]], [[Chile]]<ref>{{Cite web |title=Pedro Pascal Profile |url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/celebrity/pedro_pascal |access-date= April 2, 2022 |agency=Rotten Tomatoes|archive-date= April 2, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220402214627/https://www.rottentomatoes.com/celebrity/pedro_pascal |url-status=live }}</ref> to child psychologist Verónica Pascal Ureta and fertility doctor José Balmaceda Riera.<ref>{{cite news |last=Ito |first=Robert |title=A Lethal Prince, Even if a Bit Clumsy: Pedro Pascal Becomes Red Viper on 'Game of Thrones' |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2014/03/30/arts/television/pedro-pascal-becomes-red-viper-on-game-of-thrones.html?_r=0 |access-date= May 27, 2014 |newspaper=[[The New York Times]] |date= March 28, 2014 |archive-date= November 12, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112020115/http://www.nytimes.com/2014/03/30/arts/television/pedro-pascal-becomes-red-viper-on-game-of-thrones.html?_r=0 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="nytsarticle">{{cite web |last=Koblin |first=John |title=Pedro Pascal: Making It at 41 |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/02/03/fashion/mens-style/pedro-pascal-great-wall-game-of-thrones-narcos-late-success.html |access-date= July 4, 2019 |newspaper=[[The New York Times]] |date= February 3, 2017 |archive-date= December 29, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201229040531/https://www.nytimes.com/2017/02/03/fashion/mens-style/pedro-pascal-great-wall-game-of-thrones-narcos-late-success.html |url-status=live}}</ref> His paternal grandmother was born in [[Palma de Mallorca]], [[Spain]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Palma |first=Redacción |date=2017-09-21 |title=El pasado mallorquín del agente Peña de Narcos |url=https://www.diariodemallorca.es/sociedad/2017/09/21/pasado-mallorquin-agente-pena-narcos-3343743.html |access-date=2023-05-30 |website=Diario de Mallorca |language=es}}</ref> He has an older sister named Javiera,<ref>{{cite web |title="Narcos" star Pedro Pascal on the mystery of Pablo Escobar's death | via=[[YouTube]] |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HC5G0bsSQtw |access-date= November 3, 2020 |archive-date= December 29, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201229040511/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HC5G0bsSQtw |url-status=live}}</ref> a younger brother named Nicolás, and a younger sister named [[Lux Pascal|Lux]], who is an actress and [[transgender]] activist.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.t13.cl/noticia/entretencion/Lucas-Balmaceda-el-hermano-del-chileno-de-Game-of-Thrones-que-llego-a-remecer-Los-80 |title=Lucas Balmaceda, el hermano del chileno de Game of Thrones que llegó a remecer Los 80 |website=t13.cl |access-date= January 13, 2018 |archive-date= November 11, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201111204523/https://www.t13.cl/noticia/entretencion/Lucas-Balmaceda-el-hermano-del-chileno-de-Game-of-Thrones-que-llego-a-remecer-Los-80 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Pedro Pascal Sweetly Supports His Sister Lux After She Comes Out as a Trans Woman: 'Mi Corazón' |url=https://people.com/movies/pedro-pascal-supports-sister-lux-comes-out-trans-woman/ |website=People |date= February 9, 2021 |access-date= February 12, 2021 |archive-date= February 11, 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210211212045/https://people.com/movies/pedro-pascal-supports-sister-lux-comes-out-trans-woman/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Pascal's mother was the cousin of [[Andrés Pascal Allende]], the nephew of socialist [[President of Chile|Chilean President]] [[Salvador Allende]] (through his sister [[Laura Allende|Laura]]). Andrés was an early leader of the [[Revolutionary Left Movement (Chile)|Movement of the Revolutionary Left]], a militant [[far-left]] organisation.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.latercera.com/noticia/pedro-pascal-punto/ |title=Pedro Pascal, en su punto |website=La Tercera |date=  September 1, 2017 |access-date= January 10, 2021 |archive-date= February 24, 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210224073623/https://www.latercera.com/noticia/pedro-pascal-punto/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

According to Pascal, his parents were devout followers of Allende and active in resistance groups against the Pinochet dictatorship.<ref name="reddit">Pascal, Pedro. (25 May 2014). Reddit. [https://www.reddit.com/r/IAmA/comments/26gtvt/i_am_actor_pedro_pascal_i_play_oberyn_in_game_of I am actor Pedro Pascal. I play Oberyn in Game of Thrones, Ask me anything.] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201110003947/https://www.reddit.com/r/IAmA/comments/26gtvt/i_am_actor_pedro_pascal_i_play_oberyn_in_game_of/ |date=November 10, 2020 }}</ref> Because of this, nine months after his birth, his family sought refuge in the [[Venezuela]]n embassy in Santiago, and later received political asylum in [[Denmark]].<ref name="people"/><ref name=OrangeCoast>{{cite news |last=Broeske |first=Pat H. |title=The Viper Prince |url=http://www.orangecoast.com/features/2014/04/28/the-viper-prince |access-date= May 27, 2014 |publisher=Orange Coast |date= April 28, 2014 |archive-date= June 2, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140602035249/http://www.orangecoast.com/features/2014/04/28/the-viper-prince |url-status=live}}</ref> Ultimately, the family moved to the United States, where Pascal was raised in [[Orange County, California]], and [[San Antonio, Texas]].<ref>{{cite news |last=McIntyre |first=Gina |title='Game of Thrones': Red Viper actor Pedro Pascal hates spoilers too |url=http://herocomplex.latimes.com/tv/game-of-thrones-red-viper-actor-pedro-pascal-hates-spoilers-too/ |access-date= May 27, 2014 |newspaper=[[Los Angeles Times]] |date= May 12, 2014 |archive-date= September 8, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180908015642/https://herocomplex.latimes.com/tv/game-of-thrones-red-viper-actor-pedro-pascal-hates-spoilers-too/ |url-status=live}}</ref> By the time he was eight years old, his family regularly visited Chile to see his 34 cousins.<ref name="variety">{{cite magazine |last=Vary |first=Adam B. |title=Pedro Pascal on Fame and 'The Mandalorian': 'Can We Cut the S— and Talk About the Child?' |url=https://variety.com/2020/tv/news/pedro-pascal-the-mandalorian-star-wars-wonder-woman-1984-1234803468/ |access-date= January 1, 2021 |magazine=Variety |date= October 14, 2020 |archive-date= October 15, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201015194622/https://variety.com/2020/tv/news/pedro-pascal-the-mandalorian-star-wars-wonder-woman-1984-1234803468/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

Pascal participated in competitive swimming in his early years and even reached the state championships in Texas at age 11. However, he stopped swimming competitively after discovering his interest in drama class.<ref name="reddit"/> He pursued acting at the [[Orange County School of the Arts]] and graduated in 1993, before attending [[New York University]]'s [[Tisch School of the Arts]], where he graduated in 1997.<ref name=OrangeCoast/><ref name="ETW">{{cite web |title=ETW Alumni |url=https://tisch.nyu.edu/drama/about/studios/experimental-theatre-wing/alumni |website=[[New York University]] |access-date= January 1, 2021 |archive-date= January 19, 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210119205137/https://tisch.nyu.edu/drama/about/studios/experimental-theatre-wing/alumni |url-status=live }}</ref> In 1995, his father was indicted by a federal grand jury for his involvement in events at a fertility clinic he ran with two others.<ref name="nytsarticle"/><ref name=":0">{{cite news |last1=Sims |first1=Calvin |title=Fertility Clinics in Chile: A Tale of a Doctor Fleeing U.S. Law |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1996/04/26/world/fertility-clinics-in-chile-a-tale-of-a-doctor-fleeing-us-law.html |agency=nytimes.com |newspaper=[[The New York Times]] |date= April 26, 1996 |access-date= February 12, 2021 |archive-date=  January 5, 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210105191300/https://www.nytimes.com/1996/04/26/world/fertility-clinics-in-chile-a-tale-of-a-doctor-fleeing-us-law.html |url-status=live }}</ref> Following this, Pascal's parents and two youngest siblings returned to Chile. Pascal maintains that his father did nothing wrong.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Koblin |first=John |date= February 3, 2017 |title=Pedro Pascal: Making It at 41 |newspaper=[[The New York Times]] |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/02/03/fashion/mens-style/pedro-pascal-great-wall-game-of-thrones-narcos-late-success.html |access-date= May 17, 2022 |archive-date= December 29, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201229040531/https://www.nytimes.com/2017/02/03/fashion/mens-style/pedro-pascal-great-wall-game-of-thrones-narcos-late-success.html |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Farinh |first=Ricardo |date= October 2, 2020 |title=De refugiado a estrela da televisão: a jornada de Pedro Pascal para chegar a Hollywood |work=NiT |url=https://www.nit.pt/cultura/de-refugiado-estrela-da-televisao-jornada-de-pedro-pascal-para-chegar-hollywood |access-date= May 17, 2022 |archive-date= July 20, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220720034740/https://www.nit.pt/cultura/de-refugiado-estrela-da-televisao-jornada-de-pedro-pascal-para-chegar-hollywood |url-status=live }}</ref> His mother committed suicide in 1999.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Gilson |first=Hilary |date= June 15, 2010 |title=José Pedro Balmaceda (1948- ) |url=https://embryo.asu.edu/pages/jose-pedro-balmaceda-1948 |access-date= May 4, 2022 |archive-date= April 19, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220419155718/https://embryo.asu.edu/pages/jose-pedro-balmaceda-1948 |url-status=live }}</ref> After her death, he began using her surname professionally as a tribute to her and because he felt that Americans had difficulty pronouncing his original surname, Balmaceda.<ref name="people">{{cite web |title=The Mandalorian's Pedro Pascal Credits His Success to His Mom, Who Died Before He Became Famous |url=https://people.com/tv/the-mandalorian-pedro-pascal-credits-his-success-to-his-mom/ |date= November 13, 2020 |access-date= January 1, 2021 |website=People |archive-date= December 12, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201212035519/https://people.com/tv/the-mandalorian-pedro-pascal-credits-his-success-to-his-mom/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name="variety" />

== Career ==
Pascal has appeared in several television series, including ''[[Buffy the Vampire Slayer]]'', ''[[The Good Wife]]'', ''[[Homeland (TV series)|Homeland]]'', ''[[The Mentalist]]'', ''[[Law & Order: Criminal Intent]], [[Law & Order: Special Victims Unit]],'' and ''[[Graceland (TV series)|Graceland]]''.<ref>{{cite news |title=''The Good Wife'' Actor Checks Into USA's ''Graceland'' in Major Arc |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/graceland-pedro-pascal-joins-386618 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |last=Ng |first=Philiana |access-date= May 30, 2013 |date= November 5, 2012 |archive-date= December 29, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201229040507/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/graceland-pedro-pascal-joins-386618 |url-status=live}}</ref> He was cast in the pilot for the [[Wonder Woman (2011 TV pilot)|2011 ''Wonder Woman'' television adaptation]],<ref>{{Cite web |last=Guthrie |first=Marisa |date= March 3, 2011 |title=Pedro Pascal Joins NBC's 'Wonder Woman' Pilot |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/tv/tv-news/pedro-pascal-joins-nbcs-wonder-164014/ |access-date= July 18, 2021 |website=The Hollywood Reporter |language=en-US |archive-date= July 18, 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210718145651/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/tv/tv-news/pedro-pascal-joins-nbcs-wonder-164014/ |url-status=live }}</ref> but the show was not picked up. In June 2013, he was cast as [[Oberyn Martell]] in the [[Game of Thrones (season 4)|fourth season]] of the [[HBO]] series ''[[Game of Thrones]]''.<ref name="EW.com 28 June 2013">{{cite magazine |last=Hibberd |first=James |title=''Game of Thrones'' casts major season 4 role: Oberyn the Red Viper |url=http://insidetv.ew.com/2013/06/28/thrones-red-viper-oberyn/ |access-date=  June 30, 2013 |magazine=Entertainment Weekly |date= June 28, 2013 |archive-date= December 29, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201229040451/https://ew.com/article/2013/06/28/thrones-red-viper-oberyn/ |url-status=live}}</ref> Pascal stated that he was a huge fan of ''Game of Thrones'' before being cast as Oberyn and was ecstatic to join.<ref name="reddit"/> In 2015, Pascal was cast in the role of U.S. [[Drug Enforcement Administration|DEA]] agent [[Javier Peña]] in the [[Netflix]] original show ''[[Narcos]]''. In the 2015 movie, ''[[Bloodsucking Bastards]]'', Pascal portrayed the vampire Max.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Miska |first1=Brad |title=INDIE'Bloodsucking Bastards' Turns Cast Into Vamps |url=https://bloody-disgusting.com/indie/3289705/bloodsucking-bastards-turns-cast-into-vamps/ |date= April 21, 2014 |website=bloody-disgusting.com |access-date= June 7, 2017 |archive-date= December 29, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201229040442/https://bloody-disgusting.com/indie/3289705/bloodsucking-bastards-turns-cast-into-vamps/ |url-status=live}}</ref>

[[File:Pedro Pascal SDCC 2014.jpg|thumb|upright|Pascal at the 2014 [[San Diego Comic Con]]]]

Pascal has extensive stage experience as both an actor and director; he received the Los Angeles Drama Critics Circle Award and [[Back Stage Garland Awards|Garland Award]] for his role in the [[International City Theater]] production of ''Orphans'', and has performed in classical and contemporary works. In 2010, he wrote a play, directed by [[Sarah Silverman]], ''Flaca Loves Bone'', about four siblings who meet in a snowy wood to uncover a family secret.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Pedro Pascal |url=https://www.doollee.com/PlaywrightsP/pascal-pedro.php |access-date= February 26, 2023 |website=www.doollee.com |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221210015015/https://www.doollee.com/PlaywrightsP/pascal-pedro.php |archive-date= December 10, 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref> He made his directorial debut with play ''underneathmybed'' in 2008. He also directed ''Yosemite'' and ''Killing Play'' at [[Rattlestick Playwrights Theater]].<ref>{{Cite web |date= December 15, 2011 |title=RATTLESTICK PLAYWRIGHTS THEATER to present World Premiere of "YOSEMITE" by Daniel Talbott |url=https://www.omdkc.com/rattlestick-playwrights-theater-to-present-world-premiere-of-yosemite-by-da/ |access-date= February 26, 2023 |website=DKC/O&M |language=en-US |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171231201948/https://www.omdkc.com/rattlestick-playwrights-theater-to-present-world-premiere-of-yosemite-by-da/ |archive-date= December 31, 2017 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |author=BWW News Desk |title=Rattlestick Playwrights' underneathmybed Closes 10/10 |url=https://www.broadwayworld.com/off-broadway/article/Rattlestick-Playwrights-underneathmybed-Closes-1010-20101010 |access-date= February 26, 2023 |website=BroadwayWorld.com |language=en |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230226145858/https://www.broadwayworld.com/off-broadway/article/Rattlestick-Playwrights-underneathmybed-Closes-1010-20101010 |archive-date=  February 26, 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> He is a member of New York City's [[LAByrinth Theater Company]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Company Members |url=http://www.labtheater.org/companymembers/memberslist.html |website=[[LAByrinth Theater Company]] |access-date= June 4, 2014 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131019045129/http://www.labtheater.org/companymembers/memberslist.html |archive-date= October 19, 2013}}</ref> Pascal made his Broadway debut in February 2019 in an adaptation of ''[[King Lear]]'' with [[Glenda Jackson]] and [[Ruth Wilson]].<ref>{{Cite web |last1=12 September |first1=David Canfield |last2=EDT |first2=2018 at 10:31 AM |title=Ruth Wilson, Pedro Pascal, more to star opposite Glenda Jackson in 'King Lear' on Broadway |url=https://ew.com/theater/2018/09/12/ruth-wilson-pedro-pascal-king-lear/ |access-date= April 15, 2022 |website=EW.com |language=en |archive-date= April 15, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220415193039/https://ew.com/theater/2018/09/12/ruth-wilson-pedro-pascal-king-lear/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

In April 2015, Pascal co-starred with [[Heidi Klum]] in the music video for [[Sia]]'s "[[Fire Meet Gasoline]]".<ref>{{cite web |last1=Gordon |first1=Jeremy |title=Sia's "Fire Meet Gasoline" Used in Video Starring Heidi Klum, "Game of Thrones" Actor Pedro Pascal |url=https://pitchfork.com/news/59388-sias-fire-meet-gasoline-used-in-video-starring-heidi-klum-game-of-thrones-actor-pedro-pascal/ |website=[[Pitchfork Media]] |access-date= April 23, 2015 |date=  April 23, 2015 |archive-date= December 29, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201229040539/https://pitchfork.com/news/59388-sias-fire-meet-gasoline-used-in-video-starring-heidi-klum-game-of-thrones-actor-pedro-pascal/ |url-status=live}}</ref> In 2017, he starred as Agent Whiskey in [[Matthew Vaughn]]'s ''[[Kingsman: The Golden Circle]]'' and as mercenary Pero<ref>{{Cite web |date= February 15, 2017 |title=Pedro Pascal goes from 'Game of Thrones' to 'Great Wall' |url=https://www.dailynews.com/arts-and-entertainment/20170215/pedro-pascal-goes-from-game-of-thrones-to-great-wall |access-date= May 26, 2022 |website=Daily News |language=en-US |archive-date= May 15, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170515170352/http://www.dailynews.com/arts-and-entertainment/20170215/pedro-pascal-goes-from-game-of-thrones-to-great-wall |url-status=live }}</ref> Tovar in ''[[The Great Wall (film)|The Great Wall]]''.{{citation needed|date=May 2023}} In 2018, Pascal co-starred as Dave York, the primary antagonist in the thriller sequel film ''[[The Equalizer 2]]''; the film starred [[Denzel Washington]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Ford |first1=Rebecca |title='The Equalizer' Sequel Adds Pedro Pascal |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/equalizer-sequel-adds-pedro-pascal-1030230 |access-date= August 22, 2017 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]] |date= August 21, 2017 |archive-date= August 24, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170824092247/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/equalizer-sequel-adds-pedro-pascal-1030230 |url-status=live }}</ref>

Since 2019, Pascal has portrayed the [[The Mandalorian (character)|title role]] in ''[[The Mandalorian]]'', the first live-action ''[[Star Wars]]'' television series, which debuted on [[Disney+]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/11/the-mandalorian-star-wars-pedro-pascal-talks-disney-streaming-series-1202501235/ |title='The Mandalorian' Targets Pedro Pascal For Title Role In Disney+ Series |last=Boucher |first=Geoff |website=Deadline |date= November 13, 2018 |access-date= November 14, 2018 |archive-date= November 13, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181113232557/https://deadline.com/2018/11/the-mandalorian-star-wars-pedro-pascal-talks-disney-streaming-series-1202501235/ |url-status=live}}</ref> The same year, he starred as Francisco "Catfish" Morales in the Netflix heist drama ''[[Triple Frontier (film)|Triple Frontier]]''.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://deadline.com/2017/07/netflix-triple-frontier-mark-wahlberg-charlie-hunnam-garrett-hedlund-pedro-pascal-1202126476/ |title=Netflix 'Triple Frontier' Eyes August Start; Mark Wahlberg, Charlie Hunnam, Garrett Hedlund, Pedro Pascal In Talks |last1=Fleming |first1=Mike Jr. |date= July 26, 2017 |work=Deadline |access-date= July 30, 2017 |archive-date= October 3, 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211003071903/https://deadline.com/2017/07/netflix-triple-frontier-mark-wahlberg-charlie-hunnam-garrett-hedlund-pedro-pascal-1202126476/ |url-status=live }}</ref> He played [[Maxwell Lord]] in the [[DC Extended Universe]] film ''[[Wonder Woman 1984]]'', directed by [[Patty Jenkins]]. Following delays due to the [[COVID-19 pandemic]], the film was released to theaters and [[HBO Max]] on 25 December 2020.<ref name="PascalCast">{{cite news |last1=Kroll |first1=Justin |title='Narcos' Star Pedro Pascal Lands Key Role in 'Wonder Woman' Sequel (EXCLUSIVE) |url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/pedro-pascal-wonder-woman-sequel-narcos-1202738657/ |access-date= May 29, 2018 |work=Variety |date= March 28, 2018 |archive-date= March 29, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180329010138/http://variety.com/2018/film/news/pedro-pascal-wonder-woman-sequel-narcos-1202738657/ |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="Hex">{{cite web |title=Fandom twitter |url=https://twitter.com/getFANDOM/status/1187374105118609409 |website=Twitter |access-date= October 26, 2019 |archive-date= December 29, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201229040441/https://twitter.com/getFANDOM/status/1187374105118609409 |url-status=live}}</ref>

In February 2021, Pascal was cast in the [[Judd Apatow]] film ''[[The Bubble (2022 film)|The Bubble]]''.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Kroll |first=Justin |date= February 9, 2021 |title=Judd Apatow Sets All-Star Cast For New Netflix Comedy 'The Bubble'; Karen Gillan, Keegan-Michael Key, Maria Bakalova & Pedro Pascal Among 9 Set To Join Ensemble |url=https://deadline.com/2021/02/judd-apatow-sets-netflix-the-bubble-karen-gillian-keegan-michael-key-pedro-pascal-and-leslie-mann-among-those-set-to-join-ensemble-1234690118/ |access-date= April 12, 2021 |website=Deadline |language=en-US |archive-date= November 11, 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211111043352/https://deadline.com/2021/02/judd-apatow-sets-netflix-the-bubble-karen-gillian-keegan-michael-key-pedro-pascal-and-leslie-mann-among-those-set-to-join-ensemble-1234690118/ |url-status=live }}</ref> The film premiered on Netflix on 1 April 2022. Pascal co-starred with [[Nicolas Cage]] in the comedy ''[[The Unbearable Weight of Massive Talent]]'' which premiered at [[South by Southwest|SXSW]] 2022 in April.<ref>{{Cite web |last=DeFore |first=John |date= March 13, 2022 |title=Nicolas Cage in 'The Unbearable Weight of Massive Talent': Film Review {{!}} SXSW 2022 |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/movies/movie-reviews/nicolas-cage-in-the-unbearable-weight-of-massive-talent-film-sxsw-2022-1235110212/ |access-date= April 15, 2022 |website=The Hollywood Reporter |language=en-US |archive-date= April 15, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220415191536/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/movies/movie-reviews/nicolas-cage-in-the-unbearable-weight-of-massive-talent-film-sxsw-2022-1235110212/ |url-status=live }}</ref> In February 2021, Pascal was cast in the lead role of [[Joel (The Last of Us)|Joel Miller]] for the [[HBO]] adaptation of ''[[The Last of Us (TV series)|The Last of Us]]''.<ref name="Deadline Pascal">{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2021/02/pedro-pascal-star-joel-the-last-of-us-hbo-series-video-game-playstation-1234691935/ |title=Pedro Pascal To Star As Joel In 'The Last of Us' HBO Series Based On Video Game |last=Andreeva |first=Nellie |work=[[Deadline Hollywood|Deadline]] |publisher=[[Penske Media Corporation]] |date=February 10, 2021 |access-date=February 11, 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210211034813/https://deadline.com/2021/02/pedro-pascal-star-joel-the-last-of-us-hbo-series-video-game-playstation-1234691935/ |archive-date= February 11, 2021 |url-status=live}}</ref> Pascal reportedly received $600,000 per episode.<ref>{{Cite web |last1=Otterson |first1=Michael Schneider,Joe |last2=Schneider |first2=Michael |last3=Otterson |first3=Joe |date= August 18, 2021 |title=Streaming Boom Keeps TV Salaries at Heady Levels: Here's What Kate Winslet, Jason Sudeikis and More Are Earning |url=https://variety.com/2021/tv/news/tv-salaries-2021-kate-winslet-jason-sudeikis-succession-1235043291/ |access-date= April 15, 2022 |website=Variety |language=en-US |archive-date= August 18, 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210818232156/https://variety.com/2021/tv/news/tv-salaries-2021-kate-winslet-jason-sudeikis-succession-1235043291/ |url-status=live }}</ref> In November 2022, he was cast in ''[[Freaky Tales (film)|Freaky Tales]]'', to be directed by [[Anna Boden and Ryan Fleck]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Kroll |first1=Justin |title=Pedro Pascal, Ben Mendelsohn, Jay Ellis And Jack Champion Among Those Joining Ensemble Of eOne And Macro's ''Freaky Tales'' From Ryan Fleck And Anna Boden |url=https://deadline.com/2022/11/pedro-pascal-ben-mendelsoh-jay-ellis-jack-champion-eone-macros-freaky-tales-ryan-fleck-anna-boden-1235174116/ |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |access-date= November 16, 2022 |date= November 16, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221116203809/https://deadline.com/2022/11/pedro-pascal-ben-mendelsoh-jay-ellis-jack-champion-eone-macros-freaky-tales-ryan-fleck-anna-boden-1235174116/ |archive-date= November 16, 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref> In April 2023, he was added to the cast of [[Ethan Coen]]'s ''[[Drive-Away Dolls]]''.<ref>{{cite web |last1=D'Alessandro |first1=Anthony |title=Ethan Coen's Margaret Qualley & Geraldine Viswanathan ''Drive-Away Dolls'' To Park At Cinemas This Fall |url=https://deadline.com/2023/04/margaret-qualley-ethan-coen-drive-away-dolls-theatrical-release-date-1235328531/ |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |access-date= April 17, 2023 |date= April 17, 2023 |archive-date= April 17, 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230417184232/https://deadline.com/2023/04/margaret-qualley-ethan-coen-drive-away-dolls-theatrical-release-date-1235328531/ |url-status=live }}</ref> In May 2023, Pascal was cast in an upcoming sequel of ''[[Gladiator (2000 film)|Gladiator]]''.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Kroll |first=Justin |date=2023-05-01 |title=Pedro Pascal Joins Ridley Scott’s ‘Gladiator’ Sequel At Paramount |url=https://deadline.com/2023/05/pedro-pascal-ridley-scotts-gladiator-paramount-1235352214/ |access-date=2023-05-28 |website=Deadline |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-05-26 |title=“Esto se va a descontrolar”: Almodóvar adelantó que Pedro Pascal “está con dieta rigurosa y ejercicios brutales para conseguir cuerpo del gladiador” |url=https://www.publimetro.cl/entretenimiento/2023/05/26/esto-se-va-a-descontrolar-almodovar-adelanto-que-pedro-pascal-esta-con-dieta-rigurosa-y-ejercicios-brutales-para-conseguir-cuerpo-del-gladiador/ |access-date=2023-05-28 |website=Publimetro Chile |language=es}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Pascal is fluent in both English and Spanish and has been a resident of [[New York City]] since 1993.<ref name=OrangeCoast/> He developed a close friendship with actress [[Sarah Paulson]] soon after moving there.<ref name=Interview>{{cite web |url=https://www.interviewmagazine.com/culture/pedro-pascal |title=Pedro Pascal |author=Sarah Paulson |author-link=Sarah Paulson |date= September 18, 2014 |access-date= February 11, 2021 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210116150127/https://www.interviewmagazine.com/culture/pedro-pascal |archive-date= January 16, 2021}}</ref>

Pascal is an advocate of [[LGBT rights by country or territory|LGBTQ+ rights]]<ref>{{Cite web |last=Ennis |first=Dawn |title=This Is The Way 'The Mandalorian' Cast Gets Personal On Social Media |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/dawnstaceyennis/2020/10/30/this-is-the-way-the-mandalorian-cast-gets-personal-on-social-media/ |access-date= April 10, 2022 |website=Forbes |language=en |archive-date= April 11, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220411001948/https://www.forbes.com/sites/dawnstaceyennis/2020/10/30/this-is-the-way-the-mandalorian-cast-gets-personal-on-social-media/ |url-status=live }}</ref> and was supportive of his sister [[Lux Pascal]] when she came out as [[transgender]]. Lux said, "He has been an important part of this. He is also an artist and has been a guide. He was one of the first to give me the things that formed my identity."<ref>{{Cite web |date= February 10, 2021 |title=Pedro Pascal Sends Love To Sister Coming Out As Transgender |url=https://www.huffpost.com/entry/pedro-pascal-sister-coming-out-as-transgender_n_6023eac3c5b6d78d444b623e |access-date= April 11, 2022 |website=HuffPost |language=en |archive-date= April 11, 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220411002729/https://www.huffpost.com/entry/pedro-pascal-sister-coming-out-as-transgender_n_6023eac3c5b6d78d444b623e |url-status=live }}</ref>

Pascal identifies as an [[Agnosticism|agnostic]]<ref>{{Cite journal |date= February 23, 2017 |title=Bad Hombre Pedro Pascal |journal=Solar Magazine}}</ref> and a progressive liberal.<ref>{{Cite journal |date= August 24, 2017 |title=Narco's Pedro Pascal |journal=ShortList Magazine}}</ref> He endorsed leftist [[Gabriel Boric]] in the [[2021 Chilean presidential election]].<ref>{{Cite web |date= November 23, 2021 |title=Pedro Pascal hace público con una fotografía su apoyo a Gabriel Boric |url=https://www.t13.cl/noticia/elecciones-2021/tendencias/pedro-pascal-apoyo-gabriel-boric-elecciones-segunda-vuelta-23-11-2021 |last= |first= |access-date= November 29, 2021 |work=[[Teletrece]] |archive-date= November 29, 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211129212634/https://www.t13.cl/noticia/elecciones-2021/tendencias/pedro-pascal-apoyo-gabriel-boric-elecciones-segunda-vuelta-23-11-2021 |url-status=live |language=es}}</ref>

